fellowsList.name: Kenya Bingham-Psalms, MD
fellowsList.background: First-generation college graduate and Family Medicine resident, bilingual in English/Spanish, with interests in medical missions, global health, and HIV health equity.

fellowsList.name: Zac Badii, MD
fellowsList.background: USC-trained Family Medicine physician, committed to addressing sex disparities in HIV prevention and social determinants of health through community-centered research.

fellowsList.name: Licho Aguilera, MD
fellowsList.background: Nawat and non-binary physician focusing on decolonial medicine for Black and Indigenous communities; certified HIV Specialist and HIV Clinical Leadership fellow.

fellowsList.name: Bianca Hill, MD, MPH
fellowsList.background: Family Medicine physician with MPH, experienced in HIV care in NYC and PrEP research, passionate about health equity and care for incarcerated women.

fellowsList.name: Mark Lieber, MD
fellowsList.background: Stanford-trained physician and former National Geographic producer, experienced in global HIV health systems; completed residency at Johns Hopkins Bayview.
